is the zero of the function \( f(x)= x^3 - $c0 \).
We begin with a good guess, say \( x_1 = $b0 \). Then Newton's Method proceeds
by the recursion \( x_{n+1} = x_n - \frac{f(x_n)}{f'(x_n)} \).

